{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is cross-module handoff: three collectors plus the report-assembly path feeding the summary step. A unit test of a single formatter/parser would miss wiring errors where one source is dropped. Real OS/network is not required for this specific behavior because source clients can be stubbed at module boundaries, and correctness does not depend on model output content.","test_description":"Wire the real orchestrator/report builder with three source adapters replaced by deterministic in-process fakes returning distinct sentinel payloads; replace summary generator with a capture stub. Assert the payload passed into summary generation contains all three source sections and expected key fields, catching omission/overwrite/order-mapping bugs in module integration.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Higher levels rejected: System is disqualified because behavior text is about \"content passed\" (internal handoff), not real network/OS effects; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because no requirement here depends on evaluating model decisions.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This failure appears when collector error handling, section rendering, and pipeline continuation interact. A pure unit test on one function is too narrow. Minimum infra is still in-process: simulate one source failure via adapter stub/exception and verify graceful degradation behavior across modules.","test_description":"Run report generation with two source fakes returning data and one source fake raising timeo