faces: source APIs plus outbound email and inbox receipt. In-process mocks can hide SMTP/API auth, transport, formatting, and delivery-path failures. The assertion is delivery success end-to-end, so real infrastructure is required.","test_description":"Run scheduled/report job in a staging-like environment against reachable test endpoints and real email delivery service, sending to a test inbox account. Assert job completes, message is received by configured recipient, and body/attachment corresponds to generated report artifact.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Agentic rejected based on behavior text focus: \"reaches ... inbox correctly\" tests transport/system E2E, not summary semantic quality. Workflow rejected because no requirement here evaluates multiple model decisions in sequence.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior depends on real filesystem persistence plus run-to-run scheduling/retry semantics and external delivery outage conditions. Mocks often miss OS/file-permission/path/timestamp/state-carryover issues that cause real failures between scheduled executions.","test_description":"Force email service outage in a test environment, execute scheduled run, verify report file is created on local disk with expected content/metadata, then restore service and trigger next scheduled run. Assert retry sends previously saved report and clears/updates retry state correctly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Integration rejected because behavior text explicitly requires \"saved to a local file\" and \"retried on the next scheduled run,\" which crosses OS persistence and scheduling boundaries. Agentic/Workflow rejected since correctness is retry/persistence behavior, not model decision quality.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
